sample_data.ai_summary: Eesti Energia seeks a one-year travel-insurance provider for 15.10.2025-14.10.2026; bidders must (mandatory) hold an Estonian licence to underwrite the required insurance classes and must not have any outstanding significant contract breach with Eesti Energia or any statutory exclusion grounds under § 95(1) of the Public Procurement Act.

This compliance-check document merely confirms—via a mandatory “Yes/No” radio-button—that the bidder accepts all still-unseen Eesti Energia travel-insurance tender terms for 2025-10-15 to 2026-10-14, so only insurers already licensed in Estonia and willing to bid unconditionally should proceed to download the full dossier.

Eesti Energia’s one-year group travel-insurance tender (15.10.2025-14.10.2026) is a 100 % price-only competition (lowest net-EUR offer wins) with no stated technical/qualification hurdles, so any insurer able to underwrite travel risks at the lowest cost should bid.

Eesti Energia otsib maaklerit/insurert, kes 15.10.2025-14.10.2026 pakkuda avatud poliisiga 2 100 töötaja ametireisikindlustust (kogu maailm, välja arvatud koduriik ja RU/BY/UA) 500 000 € meditsiiniabi, 75 000 € õnnetusjuhtumi ja muude kindlustuskaitsedega (terrorism, looduskatastroof, COVID-19, üle 70-a ja ohtliku töö tegijad kaetud), kus hinnatase on oluline, kuid piiratud paremate tingimuste pakkumine on lubatud, kui see hinda oluliselt ei kergita – pakkumise esitamiseks peab olema võime

Eesti Energia otsib 15.10.2025–14.10.2026 perioodiks aastast reisikindlustust; pakkumused tuleb esitada eesti keeles (võõrkeelsed koos tõlkega) ja need peavad kehtima 30 päeva, alternatiivlahendused on keelatud, osaleda võivad vaid EL/EMP/WTO riikides registreeritud kindlustusandjad (kindlustuslitsents kohustuslik).

sample_data.company_description:
TAMRO EESTI OÜ – pharmaceutical & healthcare supply-chain specialist  
Sector: Pharmaceutical & medical wholesale / 3PL logistics  
Core business: Full-line wholesale of Rx & OTC medicines, hospital & pharmacy supplies, plus value-added cold-chain, GDP warehousing and last-mile distribution across Estonia.  
Target market: Public & private hospitals, hospital pharmacies, community pharmacy chains, primary-care clinics, veterinary wholesalers, governmental health & emergency stock programs.  
Key capabilities: GDP-licensed, temperature-controlled (2-8 °C & 15-25 °C) storage, 24 h on-call deliveries, serialisation & tamper-evident compliance, data-driven demand forecasting, reimbursement & tender management, bilingual customer service.  
Scale: Estonian subsidiary of Tamro Group (leading Nordic pharma distributor); 50-99 employees, nationwide coverage, >30 000 SKUs in portfolio, ISO 9001 certified.

Sevenline OÜ is an Estonia-based digital marketing holding company that orchestrates end-to-end online growth for small and mid-sized businesses across the Baltics and EU.  
Through its flagship subsidiary DreamGrow Digital (Google-certified Premier Partner), Sevenline delivers: SEO, Google Ads & PPC, conversion-focused web development, Google Analytics/GA4 set-up & deep-dive reporting, strategic digital road-mapping, domain registration and secure hosting.

Industry focus: digital marketing & martech services, e-commerce enablement, data-driven advertising.  
Core customers: local SMEs, start-ups and export-oriented brands that need measurable leads, online sales and cost-efficient customer acquisition.

Key capabilities: multilingual campaign management (ET/EN/RU), ROI-centric performance marketing, CRO, full-funnel analytics, 20+ years collective experience, proven track record in B2B & B2C verticals.  
Company size: micro-enterprise (<10 employees) operating on a project-based network model with scalable specialist resources.

Sevenline OÜ – Digital Marketing & Web-Services Accelerator  
Estonia-based micro-enterprise (≤10 staff) focused on data-driven internet marketing, delivered mainly through its subsidiary DreamGrow Digital, Estonia’s leading Google-certified agency.  
Core activities: SEO, Google Ads/AdWords management, web analytics (Google Analytics setup & deep-dives), strategic digital marketing consulting, website development, domain registration and hosting.  
Industry: Digital marketing / ICT services.  
Target market: SMEs and public-sector organisations in the Baltic-Nordic region seeking measurable online growth—more traffic, qualified leads and e-commerce sales.  
Key capabilities: full-funnel performance campaigns, conversion-rate optimisation, Google stack mastery, transparent KPI reporting, 15+ years regional track record, bilingual Estonian/English service.
